hwVoip.description: This MIB module defines MIB objects which provides MGCP management.

hwMgcpParaTable.name: hwMgcpParaTable
hwMgcpParaTable.description: This table is used to set the MGCP dynamic parameters. The index of this table is hwMgcpParaMgId.

hwMgcpParaEntry.name: hwMgcpParaEntry
hwMgcpParaEntry.description: This table is used to set the MGCP dynamic parameters. The index of this entry is hwMgcpParaMgId.

hwMgcpParaRetranIntervalTimer.name: hwMgcpParaRetranIntervalTimer
hwMgcpParaRetranIntervalTimer.description: Indicates the maximum re-transmission interval of MGCP messages.

hwMgcpParaMaxRetranTimes.name: hwMgcpParaMaxRetranTimes
hwMgcpParaMaxRetranTimes.description: Indicates the maximum re-transmission times of MGCP messages.

hwMgcpParaProvRspDelay.name: hwMgcpParaProvRspDelay
hwMgcpParaProvRspDelay.description: Indicates the delay of the MGCP stack timer for receiving the provisional responses.

hwMgcpParaAtMostOnceTimer.name: hwMgcpParaAtMostOnceTimer
hwMgcpParaAtMostOnceTimer.description: Indicates the length of the At-most-once timer of the MGCP stack.

hwMgcpParaEnbProyRsp.name: hwMgcpParaEnbProyRsp
hwMgcpParaEnbProyRsp.description: Indicates whether the MGCP stack supports transmitting provisional responses. Options: 1. no(1) - indicates that the MGCP stack not supports transmitting provisional responses 1. yes(2) - indicates that the MGCP stack supports transmitting provisional responses

hwMgcpParaEnbSdpTransParent.name: hwMgcpParaEnbSdpTransParent
hwMgcpParaEnbSdpTransParent.description: Indicates whether the MGCP stack supports partial transparent transmission of the Session Description Protocol (SDP). Options: 1. no(1) - indicates that the MGCP stack not supports partial transparent transmission of the Session Description Protocol (SDP) 1. yes(2) - indicates that the MGCP stack supports partial transparent transmission of the Session Description Protocol (SDP)

hwMgcpMedGwyConfigTable.name: hwMgcpMedGwyConfigTable
hwMgcpMedGwyConfigTable.description: This table is used to config the MGCP media gateway. The index of this table is hwMgcpMedGwyId.

hwMgcpMedGwyConfigEntry.name: hwMgcpMedGwyConfigEntry
hwMgcpMedGwyConfigEntry.description: This table is used to config the MGCP media gateway. The index of this entry is hwMgcpMedGwyId.

hwMgcpMedGwyDomainName.name: hwMgcpMedGwyDomainName
hwMgcpMedGwyDomainName.description: Domain name Parameter 0: clears the value of the parameter

hwMgcpMedGwyIPAddress.name: hwMgcpMedGwyIPAddress
hwMgcpMedGwyIPAddress.description: Indicates the IP address that the Media Gateway Controller will use to communicate with the Media Gateway.

hwMgcpMedGwyUDPPort.name: hwMgcpMedGwyUDPPort
hwMgcpMedGwyUDPPort.description: Indicates the UDP port that the Media Gateway Controller will use to communicate with the Media Gateway. The value 65535 is returned if the entry is invalid. The valid value is from 1 to 4999 in MD5500 and from 1 to 16383 in AMG5000.

hwMgcpMedGwyCodeType.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCodeType
hwMgcpMedGwyCodeType.description: Indicates the coding type. Options: 1.txt(1)-indicates that the coding type is text

hwMgcpMedGwyTransMode.name: hwMgcpMedGwyTransMode
hwMgcpMedGwyTransMode.description: Indicates the transmission mode. Options: 1.udp(2)-indicates that the transmission mode is udp

hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey.name: hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey
hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey.description: Indicates the key that is registered with the MGC, and the length of valid key input is from 8 to 32. The key cannot be modified, read, or written by the operator without authority, so the hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey and hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey must also be provided to query and modify the hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey. The conditions for querying and modifying the hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey are as follows: 1) The hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey can return the correct query result only when the hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey is correct. Otherwise, the query fails; 2) The hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey can be set successfully only when the hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey is correct. Otherwise, the setting fails. The size 0 means the parameter not configured.

hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey.name: hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey
hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey.description: Indicates the key for operating the MG. The hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey cannot be read or written. The functions of this key are as follows: 1) The hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey and hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey must be provided for modifying the hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey. The hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey can return the correct query result only when the hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey is correct. Otherwise, the query fails. The hwMgcpMedGwyRegisterKey can be set successfully only when the hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey is correct. Otherwise, the setting fails. 2) The hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey must work with the hwMgcpMedGwyOperKeyNew for modifying the hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey itself. The hwMgcpMedGwyOperKeyNew and hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey must be provided at the same time. The value of the hwMgcpMedGwyOperKeyNew can replace the value of the hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey and the hwMgcpMedGwyOperKeyNew can become the new operation key only when the hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey is correct. Otherwise, the modification fails and the hwMgcpMedGwyOperKey operation key is retained.

hwMgcpMedGwyOperKeyNew.name: hwMgcpMedGwyOperKeyNew
hwMgcpMedGwyOperKeyNew.description: Indicates the new operation key, and the length of valid key input is from 8 to 32. The hwMgcpMedGwyOperKeyNew is a temporary variable, and cannot be read. If you query one hwMgcpMedGwyOperKeyNew not configured, the system always returns a null value.

hwMgcpMedGwyAdminStatus.name: hwMgcpMedGwyAdminStatus
hwMgcpMedGwyAdminStatus.description: Indicates the administrative status for this media gateway control group. Options: 1.up(1)-indicates that the administrative status for this media gateway control group is up 2.down(2)-indicates that the administrative status for this media gateway control group is down

hwMgcpMedGwyOperStatus.name: hwMgcpMedGwyOperStatus
hwMgcpMedGwyOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operational status of the signaling link. Options: 1.up(1)-indicates that the current operational status of the signaling link is up 2.down(2)-indicates that the current operational status of the signaling link is down 3.fault(3)-indicates that the current operational status of the signaling link is fault 4.waitingAck(4)-indicates that the current operational status of the signaling link is waitingAck 5.unknown(5)-indicates that the current operational status of the signaling link is unknown 6.notStart(6)-indicates that the current operational status of the signaling link is notStart

hwMgcpMedGwyRowStatus.name: hwMgcpMedGwyRowStatus
hwMgcpMedGwyRowStatus.description: This is used to create new rows in this table, Modify existing rows, and to delete existing rows.

hwMgcpMedGwyLastChange.name: hwMgcpMedGwyLastChange
hwMgcpMedGwyLastChange.description: Indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time the associated link entered its current operational status. If the current status was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

hwMgcpMedGwyAuthMode.name: hwMgcpMedGwyAuthMode
hwMgcpMedGwyAuthMode.description: Indicates the authentication mode. Options: 1.hwmode(1)-indicates that the authentication mode is huawei mode 2.gbmode(2)-indicates that the authentication mode is global mode

hwMgcpMedGwyAuthInitialKey.name: hwMgcpMedGwyAuthInitialKey
hwMgcpMedGwyAuthInitialKey.description: Indicates the authentication initial key, and the length of valid key input is from 1 to 16. The size 0 means the parameter is not configured.

hwMgcpMedGwyAuthMgId.name: hwMgcpMedGwyAuthMgId
hwMgcpMedGwyAuthMgId.description: Indicates the authentication MG ID and the length input is from 1 to 16. The size 0 means the parameter is not configured.

hwMgcpMedGwy2833Encrypt.name: hwMgcpMedGwy2833Encrypt
hwMgcpMedGwy2833Encrypt.description: Indicates the 2833 encryption key and the length of valid key input is from 1 to 16. The size 0 means the parameter is not configured.

hwMgcpMedGwyCfgHeartBeatTimer.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCfgHeartBeatTimer
hwMgcpMedGwyCfgHeartBeatTimer.description: Indicates the configured timer of the heartbeat (s).

hwMgcpMedGwyIPAddrDhcpClientIndex.name: hwMgcpMedGwyIPAddrDhcpClientIndex
hwMgcpMedGwyIPAddrDhcpClientIndex.description: Dhcp Signal vlan id. The valid value is 1..4093,if the value is -1, the static signal ip will be used.

hwMgcpMedGwyCurDynAddrName.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCurDynAddrName
hwMgcpMedGwyCurDynAddrName.description: Current working dynamic media gateway IP name.

hwMgcpMedGwyCurIPAddress.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCurIPAddress
hwMgcpMedGwyCurIPAddress.description: Indicates the IP address that the Media Gateway current use to communicate with the Media Gateway Controller.

hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlTable.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlTable
hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlTable.description: This table is used to config the MGCP media gateway control parameters. The indexes of this table are hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlGatewayId and hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlIdx.

hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlEntry.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlEntry
hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlEntry.description: This table is used to config the MGCP media gateway control parameters. The indexes of this entry are hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlGatewayId and hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlIdx.

hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlIPAddress.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlIPAddress
hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlIPAddress.description: Indicates the IP address of the Media Gateway Controller. The value 255.255.255.255 is returned if the entry is invalid.

hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlDnsName.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlDnsName
hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlDnsName.description: Indicates the DNS name of the MGC. - means clears the value of the parameter.

hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlDnsIp.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlDnsIp
hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlDnsIp.description: Indicates the IP address that is obtained through the MGC domain name. DEFVAL { false }

hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlPort.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlPort
hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlPort.description: Indicates the UDP port of the Media Gateway Controller. The value 65535 is returned if the entry is invalid.

hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlAdminStatus.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlAdminStatus
hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlAdminStatus.description: Indicates to set the MGC as the active MGC. Options: 1. active(1) -Indicates to set the MGC as the active MGC

hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlOperStatus.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlOperStatus
hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlOperStatus.description: Indicates the status of the Media Gateway Controller (and/or) its transportLink. Options: 1. up(1) -indicates that the status of the Media Gateway Controller (and/or) its transportLink is up 2. down(2) -indicates that the status of the Media Gateway Controller (and/or) its transportLink is down 3. standby(3) -indicates that the status of the Media Gateway Controller (and/or) its transportLink is standby

hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlLastChange.name: hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlLastChange
hwMgcpMedGwyCtrlLastChange.description: Indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time the associated link entered its current operational status. If the current status was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

hwMgcpDigitmapTable.name: hwMgcpDigitmapTable
hwMgcpDigitmapTable.description: This table is used to set digitmap. The index of this table is hwMgcpDigitmapMgId.

hwMgcpDigitmapEntry.name: hwMgcpDigitmapEntry
hwMgcpDigitmapEntry.description: This table is used to set digitmap. The index of this entry is hwMgcpDigitmapMgId.

hwMgcpMgSoftParameterTable.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameterTable
hwMgcpMgSoftParameterTable.description: This table is used to set the software parameters of MGCP media gateway. The index of this table is hwMgcpMgInterfaceIndex.

hwMgcpMgSoftParameterEntry.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameterEntry
hwMgcpMgSoftParameterEntry.description: This table is used to set the software parameters of MGCP media gateway. The index of this entry is hwMgcpMgInterfaceIndex.

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter0.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter0
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter0.description: Parameter name index 0. Indicates whether the terminal ID of the MG interface is layered. Options: 1. yes(1) -indicates that the terminal ID of the MG interface is layered 2. no(2) -indicates that the terminal ID of the MG interface is not layered Default: no(2)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter1.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter1
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter1.description: Parameter name index 1. It indicates whether the ongoing calls are maintained after MG is disconnected from MGC. Options: 1. yes(1) -indicates that the ongoing calls are maintained after MG is disconnected from MGC 2. no(2) -indicates that the the ongoing calls are not maintained after MG is disconnected from MGC Default: no(2)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter2.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter2
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter2.description: Parameter name index 2. It indicates whether the MG interface supports dual homing. Options: 1. yes(1) -indicates that the MG interface supports dual homing 2. no(2) -indicates that the MG interface not supports dual homing Default: yes(1)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter3.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter3
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter3.description: Parameter name index 3. It indicates whether the heartbeat message is disabled between MG and MGC. Options: 1. yes(1) -indicates that the heartbeat message is enabled between MG and MGC 2. no(2) -indicates that the heartbeat message is disabled between MG and MGC Default: no(2)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter4.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter4
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter4.description: Parameter name index 4. It indicates whether the wildcard is used in registration. Options: 1. yes(1) -indicates that the wildcard is used in registration 2. no(2) -indicates that the wildcard is not used in registration Default: yes(1)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter5.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter5
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter5.description: Parameter name index 5. It indicates the MGC type. The value range is 1-9. Options: 1. SOFTSWITCH 2. ZTE 3. NORTEL 4. CISCO 5. SIEMENS 6. SONUS 7. ETG 8. SHANGYANG 9. MARCONI Default: 1

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter6.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter6
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter6.description: Parameter name index 6. It indicates the maximum threshold of not responding to the transmitted heartbeat message. Default: 3

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter7.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter7
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter7.description: Parameter name index 7. It indicates whether to support the report that has the MG as the endpoint name. Options: 1. yes(1) -indicates support the report that has the MG as the endpoint name 2. no(2) -indicates not support the report that has the MG as the endpoint name Default: no(2)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter8.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter8
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter8.description: Parameter name index 8. It indicates whether the port fault and auto-block is reported to the MGC. Options: 1. yes(1) -indicates that the port fault and auto-block is reported to the MGC 2. no(2) -indicates that the port fault and auto-block is not reported to the MGC Default: yes(1)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter9.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter9
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter9.description: Parameter name index 9. It is reserved in the system. Options: 1. yes(1) -yes 2. no(2) -no Default: yes(1)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter10.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter10
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter10.description: Parameter name index 10. It indicates the point-to-point fault report flag. Options: 1. yes(1) -indicates that the point-to-point fault is reported 2. no(2) -indicates that the port fault and auto-block is not reported Default: yes(1)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter11.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter11
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter11.description: Parameter name index 11. It indicates the point-to-multipoint fault report flag. Options: 1. yes(1) -indicates that the point-to-multipoint fault is reported 2. no(2) -indicates that the point-to-multipoint fault is not reported Default: no(2)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter12.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter12
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter12.description: Parameter name index 12. It indicates the local block tone type. Options: 1. busyTone(1) -indicates that the local block tone type is busyTone 2. congestionTone(2) -indicates that the local block tone type is congestionTone 3. muteTone(3) -indicates that the local block tone type is muteTone 4. userDefineTone1(4) -indicates that the local block tone type is userDefineTone1 5. userDefineTone2(5) -indicates that the local block tone type is userDefineTone2 Default: busyTone(1)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter13.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter13
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter13.description: Parameter name index 13. It indicates the remote block tone type. Options: 1. busyTone(1) -indicates that the remote block tone type is busyTone 2. congestionTone(2) -indicates that the remote block tone type is congestionTone 3. muteTone(3) -indicates that the remote block tone type is muteTone 4. userDefineTone1(4) -indicates that the remote block tone type is userDefineTone1 5. userDefineTone2(5) -indicates that the remote block tone type is userDefineTone2 Default: busyTone(1)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter14.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter14
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter14.description: Parameter name index 14. It indicates the RTP source port filtering switch. Options: 1. filter(1) -indicates that the RTP source port is filter 2. notFilter(2) -indicates that the RTP source port is not filter Default: notFilter(2)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter15.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter15
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter15.description: Parameter name index 15. It indicates the length of howl tone<1,65535>. Default:60 Unit: second

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter16.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter16
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter16.description: Parameter name index 16. Indicates whether the timer symbol (T) follows the number string reported by the signaling. Options: 1. yes(1) -indicates that the timer symbol (T) follows the number string reported by the signaling 2. no(2) -indicates that the timer symbol (T) follows the number string not reported by the signaling Default: yes(1)

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter17.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter17
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter17.description: Parameter name index 17. It indicates the duration of the timer for preventing the repeated switching between the data service and voice service after auto-switching data transparent transmission is complete. <0,65534> Default:1000 Unit: second

hwMgcpMgSoftParameter18.name: hwMgcpMgSoftParameter18
hwMgcpMgSoftParameter18.description: Parameter name index 18. Indicates whether to actively switch back to the voice service after data transparent transmission is complete. Options: 1. yes(1) -indicates actively switch back to the voice service 2. no(2) -indicates not actively switch back to the voice service Default: yes(1)

hwMgcpDmmParaTable.name: hwMgcpDmmParaTable
hwMgcpDmmParaTable.description: This table is used to set the digitmap parameters. The index of this table is hwMgcpDmmParaMgId.

hwMgcpDmmParaEntry.name: hwMgcpDmmParaEntry
hwMgcpDmmParaEntry.description: This table is used to set the digitmap parameters. The index of this entry is hwMgcpDmmParaMgId.

hwMgcpDmmParaMgcpTTimer.name: hwMgcpDmmParaMgcpTTimer
hwMgcpDmmParaMgcpTTimer.description: Indicates the length of the DMM MGCP T timer.

hwMgcpTIDConfigTable.name: hwMgcpTIDConfigTable
hwMgcpTIDConfigTable.description: This table is used to config MGCP terminal ID. The index of this table is hwMgcpTIDPrefixMgId.

hwMgcpTIDConfigEntry.name: hwMgcpTIDConfigEntry
hwMgcpTIDConfigEntry.description: This table is used to config MGCP terminal ID. The index of this entry is hwMgcpTIDPrefixMgId.

hwMgcpBraTemplateIndex.name: hwMgcpBraTemplateIndex
hwMgcpBraTemplateIndex.description: Indicates the index of the BRA TID profile.

hwMgcpPraTemplateIndex.name: hwMgcpPraTemplateIndex
hwMgcpPraTemplateIndex.description: Indicates the index of the PRA TID profile.

hwMgcpPstnTemplateIndex.name: hwMgcpPstnTemplateIndex
hwMgcpPstnTemplateIndex.description: Indicates the index of the PSTN TID profile.

hwMgcpIsNeedToConfigTID.name: hwMgcpIsNeedToConfigTID
hwMgcpIsNeedToConfigTID.description: Indicates whether the terminal ID needs to be configured for the subscriber. Bit0 (low) to bit31 (high) respectively represent PSTN, BRA, and PRA. The remaining bits are reserved. (It is unavailable in the R17.)

hwMgcpMgStatus.name: hwMgcpMgStatus
hwMgcpMgStatus.description: The status of the MGCP media gateway. Options: 1. up(1) -normal 2. down(2) -down 3. fault(3) -fault 4. waitAck(4) -waiting for ACK

hwMgcpTrapLastChangeTime.name: hwMgcpTrapLastChangeTime
hwMgcpTrapLastChangeTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the media gateway or the media gateway control entered its current status or media gateway control switched.

hwMgcpMgcStatus.name: hwMgcpMgcStatus
hwMgcpMgcStatus.description: The media gateway control status. Options: 1. up(1) -indicates that the media gateway control status is up 2. down(2) -indicates that the media gateway control status is down 3. standby(3) -indicates that the media gateway control status is standby

hwMgcpFrame.name: hwMgcpFrame
hwMgcpFrame.description: The frame where mg user is configed.

hwMgcpSlot.name: hwMgcpSlot
hwMgcpSlot.description: The slot where mg user is configed.

hwMgcpPort.name: hwMgcpPort
hwMgcpPort.description: The port where mg user is configed.

hwMgcpMgcPort.name: hwMgcpMgcPort
hwMgcpMgcPort.description: The UDP port of the MGC.

hwMgcpIsConfigTid.name: hwMgcpIsConfigTid
hwMgcpIsConfigTid.description: Indicates whether the terminal ID needs to be configured for the subscriber. Bit0 (low) to bit31 (high) respectively represent PSTN, BRA, PRA, DPNSS, DASS2, and R2. The remaining bits are reserved.

hwMgcpIsUpdateTid.name: hwMgcpIsUpdateTid
hwMgcpIsUpdateTid.description: Indicates whether the terminal ID needs to be updated for the subscriber. Bit0 (low) to bit31 (high) respectively represent PSTN, BRA, PRA, DPNSS, DASS2, and R2. The remaining bits are reserved.

hwIASMgcpResetTrap.name: hwIASMgcpResetTrap
hwIASMgcpResetTrap.description: This notification indicates that the MGCP media gateway reset result.

hwIASMgcpShutdownTrap.name: hwIASMgcpShutdownTrap
hwIASMgcpShutdownTrap.description: This notification indicates that the MGCP media gateway shutdown result.

hwIASMgcpMgStateTrap.name: hwIASMgcpMgStateTrap
hwIASMgcpMgStateTrap.description: This notification indicates that the MGCP media gateway status change.

hwIASMgcpMgcSwitchTrap.name: hwIASMgcpMgcSwitchTrap
hwIASMgcpMgcSwitchTrap.description: This notification indicates that the MGCP media gateway control switched.

hwIASMgcpMgcStateTrap.name: hwIASMgcpMgcStateTrap
hwIASMgcpMgcStateTrap.description: This notification indicates that the MGCP media gateway control status changed.

hwIASMgcpMgLableTrap.name: hwIASMgcpMgLableTrap
hwIASMgcpMgLableTrap.description: This notification indicates that the userlabel of the MGCP interface changed.

hwIASMgcpTidUpdateTrap.name: hwIASMgcpTidUpdateTrap
hwIASMgcpTidUpdateTrap.description: This notification indicates that the MGCP terminal ID updated.

hwIASMgcpMgFaultTrap.name: hwIASMgcpMgFaultTrap
hwIASMgcpMgFaultTrap.description: The MGCP media gateway is closed. This trap when a card asserts an alarm.

hwIASMgcpMgRestoreTrap.name: hwIASMgcpMgRestoreTrap
hwIASMgcpMgRestoreTrap.description: The MGCP media gateway is up. This trap when a card asserts an alarm.

hwIASMgcpAbsentResourceTrap.name: hwIASMgcpAbsentResourceTrap
hwIASMgcpAbsentResourceTrap.description: This notification indicates that the DSP resources is insufficient.
